definitions.definition: ( particle physics ) In the Standard Model , one of a number of elementary subatomic particles having fractional electric charge that forms matter . They are theorized not to exist in isolation , but only in combinations in hadrons such as neutrons and protons or in quark–gluon plasmas .
( by extension , computing , X Window System )
